721121f-a.text:
Lexington Ave., east side, north from and including East 127th to, and including 128th Streets, showing a gasoline station occupying the entire block front. The two houses, on the extreme right, are Nos. 143 and 145 East 127th Street.
March 6, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.

715468f-a.title: Manhattan: 127th Street (East) - Lexington
715468f-a.text:
121-123 East 127th Street, north side, west of Lexington Ave. Shown is the Holy Family Church, an Episcopal Spanish Mission, formerly St. Bartholomew Swedish Church.
July 31, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.

715467f-a.text:
126-128 East 127th Street, south side, west of Lexington
Avenue. No. 126 is a 22-story frame house.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 50
